## 2. Identified Gaps & Potential Issues

### A. Role Identification (ID vs Slug)
- **Issue**: The [RoleModel](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/models/role_model.dart#1-28) currently has an [id](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/utils/country_utils.dart#128-132) field but no explicit `slug` field.
- **Usage**:
  - [RoleRepository](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/repositories/role_repository.dart#5-98) methods ([updateRole](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/providers/app_state.dart#1860-1874), [deleteRole](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/repositories/collaborator_repository.dart#188-198)) expect a `slug`.
  - [UserRoleScreen](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/screens/user_role_screen.dart#7-13) passes `role.id` to [deleteRole](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/repositories/collaborator_repository.dart#188-198).
  - [CreateRoleScreen](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/screens/create_role_screen.dart#6-14) tries to use `roleData['slug']` or falls back to `roleData['id']`.
- **Risk**: If the backend uses integer IDs for [id](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/utils/country_utils.dart#128-132) and string slugs (e.g., "manager") for URL parameters, the current implementation might fail when trying to delete or update a role using the ID instead of the slug.
- **Recommendation**: Update [RoleModel](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/models/role_model.dart#1-28) to explicitly include a `slug` field if the API provides it, or verify if [id](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/utils/country_utils.dart#128-132) serves as the slug.

### B. Permission Data Consistency
- **Issue**: [CreateRoleScreen](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/screens/create_role_screen.dart#6-14) sends a list of **Permission IDs** (integers).
- **Verification**: Need to ensure the backend expects IDs for role creation/update, not permission codenames.
- **Current State**: The code collects IDs (`_selectedPermissionIds`), which is standard, but worth verifying.

### C. Role Assignment Payload
- **Issue**: [assignRoleToWorker](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/providers/app_state.dart#1926-1940) sends `{'role': roleSlug}`.
- **Verification**: [WorkerModel](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/models/worker_model.dart#1-66) has `roleSlug`. The dropdown in [UsersScreen](file:///c:/Users/ELITEX21012G2/antigravity_partnerapp/Flutter_partnerapp/lib/screens/users_screen.dart#14-20) uses `role.id` as the value.
- **Conflict**: If `role.id` is different from the role's slug, the assignment might fail.
- **Recommendation**: Ensure the dropdown uses the correct identifier (slug) expected by the backend.

